race.comment: Competitive contest. GOLDARNIE (16) shed the maiden tag over this track and trip last time out and will have derived a bunch of confidence from that breakthrough victory. Drawn to get the run of the race from the inside marble and can go back-to-back without surprising. TREVATT COURT (12) resumes from a lengthy spell but has revved up for this with two recent trials and the form she showed in her first campaign was impressive. Top-three commodity while fresh. The very well-related TIME OF MY LIFE (10) (half to 25xG1 winner Winx) strips fitter second-up from the break and may earn some minor money. BETTA BEING SINGLE (5) has only missed a drum once in six career outings and should run her usual honest race.
